- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as MRC is a task that falls under the umbrella of AI. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper discusses pruning techniques to improve the efficiency of MRC models, which is a common machine learning optimization technique. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions experiments on the TriviaQA dataset, which includes visual questions. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also less likely but possible as the paper discusses deep neural networks and their optimization.
